  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Neha, your laptop survived the coffee spill? I'm a tea person myself — no drama, just hot leaves."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Survived. Spilled on my sketchpad too. *sigh*  \nYou work with laptops a lot?  \nI’m more tea myself, but only with 3 sugars."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, that sigh sounds familiar. I get that — coffee and creativity don’t always mix. Three sugars? You take your tea seriously."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah. Tea is my *rite* of passage, basically.  \nWorking on a new design. Can’t focus after the spill.  \nCoffee’s a distraction, you know?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, rituals are powerful — your tea is clearly a focus anchor. Distractions happen. What’s your design about?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "User: A coffee cup. Irony, right? Spilled mine, designing someone else’s.  \nStill stuck on the handle. Should it be minimalist or fun?  \nYou? Any projects?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, that is a funny twist — designing cups when yours is in the trash! Handles are tricky. Minimalist or fun depends on the user, but what feels right to you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Ugh, I know. So meta.  \nI think I want fun — maybe a little twist or pattern.  \nBut my brain’s all *muddled* now.  \nYou ever design stuff?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right — fun is a safe bet when you're stuck. A twist could surprise the user in a good way. Muddled brain happens. I tweak buttons and fonts for a living — tiny things, big impact. What’s your style?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My style? Like, I’m a “form follows function” kind of gal, but with a little flair — you know, *just enough* to make it pop without screaming. Think of a calm wave with a tiny sparkle at the peak. You? Any design vibes you live by?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — calm wave with a sparkle. That’s a great way to put it. I stick to “simple is steady” — clean lines, no extra fluff. But I add little hidden details only I know about. Like a tiny tweak in a button shape. What’s your sparkle today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm. Today’s sparkle? Not sure yet. Maybe a little wave pattern in the handle — subtle, but *there*. You know? Like a secret between me and the cup. But I’m tired. Brain’s all… mush.  \nYou ever feel stuck like this?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, that kind of stuck feels heavy — like your brain is in a fog. Secret touches are the best. They make the work feel personal. What helps you break out of the mush?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Walk away. Let it sit. Come back with tea. That’s my holy trinity. Doesn’t always work, but it’s my go-to. You? How do you shake the fog?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, tea helps me too — though I usually add a fourth step: sketching something silly to laugh at. Walk away, come back, tea, and a bit of nonsense. What’s your silly sketch?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Silly sketch? Once drew a robot sipping tea with a tiny mustache. Just… random. But hey, it worked. Brain’s still mush, but I’ll take it. Maybe a robot-themed coffee cup?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, a robot with a mustache — that’s a great kind of nonsense. Robot-themed cup could be your sparkle. What if the handle had little gears? Would that pop?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Gears in the handle… *maybe*. Not sure if that’s sparkle or just noise. Brain’s too mush to decide. Think I’ll sleep on it. Or tea on it. Gotta go, maybe find a cafe. Talk later?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right — gears could be the spark or the clutter. Let your brain rest — or overstimulate with too much tea! A cafe sounds perfect. Talk soon. Tell me how the cup turns out?"
    }
  ],
